OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Fri 26 Jun to Sun 5 Jul
OL,6,FFairly changeable conditions at first
OL,7,Fwith periods of rain and showers,
OL,8,Fespecially in the west, and there
OL,9,Fcould be some thundery outbreaks at
OL,10,Ftimes. There will likely be some drier
OL,11,Fand brighter spells though. Into July
OL,12,Fchangeable conditions are likely to
OL,13,Fcontinue as Atlantic lows move in from
OL,14,Fthe west, but with transient periods
OL,15,Fof high pressure. This will lead to
OL,16,Fspells of rain and cloud interspersed
OL,17,Fwith more settled periods.
OL,18,FTemperatures remain widely above
OL,19,Faverage, and the far southeast may
OL,20,Fretain some of the hot temperatures at
OL,21,Ffirst, but likely cooler than the
OL,22,Fpreceding few days.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
